Page Brooks was born Lisa Charise Page, on November 23, 1962, in Detroit, Michigan, the daughter of Charles Warren Harris.
Her music career started in 1986, with the female black gospel quartet, Witness.
She commenced her solo music recording career in 1997, with the studio album, More Than You'll Ever Know, that was released on April 8, 1997, from A&M Records.

Her subsequent studio album, Lisa Page Brooks, was released on July 31, 2001, with Air Gospel.
The third album, Strong, was released on October 20, 2009, by Habakkuk Music, and this album peaked at No. 18 on the Billboard Gospel Albums chart.
She released, Ready, on June 4, 2013, where this album peaked at No. 17 on the Billboard Gospel Albums chart.
